The Study Planner Website is a simple web-based application designed to help students plan, organize, and manage their study schedules efficiently.
Many students struggle with time management and often forget what subject to study and when. This project solves that problem by providing a clear and structured way to plan daily and weekly study activities.

The website is developed using basic web technologies such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, making it easy to understand and suitable for beginners who are learning web development.

ğŸ” How the Website Works

The website provides an input form where the user can enter:

Subject name (what they plan to study)

Day of the week

Time duration for studying that subject

When the user clicks the â€œAdd to Scheduleâ€ button:

JavaScript collects the entered data.

The input values are validated to ensure no field is left empty.

The data is then dynamically added to a table.

The table displays the complete weekly study schedule in a clear format.

This allows the user to quickly view and manage their study plan.

âœ¨ Features Explained

User-Friendly Interface
The interface is clean and simple so that even non-technical users can use it without confusion.

Dynamic Schedule Management
The schedule table updates instantly without reloading the page, using JavaScript DOM manipulation.

Weekly Planning
Users can plan their studies for different days of the week, helping them maintain consistency.

Beginner-Friendly Code
The code is written in a simple structure with basic logic, making it easy for students to understand and modify.

No External Dependencies
The website runs directly in any modern web browser without requiring internet access or installations.

